
	README

Show how to create a NodeJS application using express, and deploy it into EC2 using deploy.

Follow the steps below:

1. create a nodeJS project called node-project1 using Express at your machine.

2. enter node-project1 directory, create a new file called Procfile

3. edit package.json

4. upload node-project1 into github.com

5. create a deploy.conf for the deploy application

6. run the following command to deploy app (node-project1) into EC2 instance

	deploy live setup
	deploy live

7. visit EC2 instance DNS to see the result


Any questions, please feel free to contact me at boyu2011@gmail.com

BoYu
